    <body>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">External </span>The external project architecture has to do with your projects as entities, their structures, and what is <span class="EmphasisItalic">outside</span> of them. This includes the external processes, tools, and other factors surrounding your projects—such as source control, task management, templates, and more. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Architecture/External-Architecture/External-Architecture.htm">External Project Architecture</MadCap:xref>.</li>
            <li>
                <span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Internal </span>The internal project architecture has to do with the structure of files and use of features <span class="EmphasisItalic">inside</span> a Flare project. It includes things such as naming conventions, folders, and structuring the project with snippets, conditions, variables and more. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Architecture/Internal-Architecture/Internal-Architecture.htm">Internal Project Architecture</MadCap:xref>.</li>
        </ul>
    </body>
